Questions:
What is the primary goal of the research study titled "Improving Care Coordination for Adolescents and Young Adults With Cancer: Implementing a Bridge Between Needs and Services"?
A) To provide financial assistance to adolescents and young adults with cancer;
B) To evaluate the effectiveness of a new chemotherapy drug;
C) To gather feedback on an intervention designed to assess and address the needs of adolescents and young adults with cancer;
D) To compare different cancer treatment methods in terms of patient recovery times.

Correct answer: C

If you experience a research-related injury or have questions about your rights as a participant in the study, whom should you contact?

A) The principal investigator, Sarah Birken, PhD;
B) The Institutional Review Board (IRB) chairman;
C) The Research Subject Advocate at Wake Forest;
D) Your personal healthcare provider.

Correct answer: B) The Institutional Review Board (IRB) chairman;
